This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel and efficient recomputation method for reducing memory consumption during backpropagation in neural networks. It also uses dynamic programming to solve the problem of minimizing computational overhead under a fixed memory budget constraint, which is a common optimization problem in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as these fields often involve the use of neural networks and optimization techniques.
